\subsection{Levelt matrices of a hypergeometric family}
\begin{definition}\label{hgm.levelt_matrices}
\uses{hgm.defining_parameters,hgm.familes,hgm.monodromy}
The {{KNOWL('hgm.monodromy', 'monodromy representation')}} associated to a {{KNOWL('hgm.familes', 'hypergeometric family')}} is generated by two matrices $h_{\infty}$ and $h_0$ describing the local monodromy around $\infty$ and $0$, respectively.  The characteristic polynomial of $h_{\infty}$ is $\prod_j (T - e^{2\pi i \alpha_j})$ and of $h_0$ is $\prod_j (T - e^{2\pi i \beta_j})$, where $(\alpha_j)$ and $(\beta_j)$ are from the {{KNOWL('hgm.defining_parameters', 'defining parameters')}} of the family.  The choice of matrices satisfying this condition is determined up to simultaneous conjugacy.

The presentation used here is due to Levelt \cite{MR:0145108}.
\end{definition}


